{"task_summary":"Rotate a square matrix 90 degrees clockwise","approach":"I used two nested for loops. I created a temporary variable to store each value in the original matrix. I then iterated through the matrix and assigned the temporary variable equal to each value on its corresponding row and column.","code":"def rotate_matrix(m):
    temp = 0
    newMatrix = [[0] * len(m) for x in range(len(m))]
    for i in m:
        for j in range(len(i)):
            newMatrix[j][len(newMatrix)-1-i] = i[j]

    return newMatrix

